<TITLE> Stormy weather beats the heat and humidity </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 8 (bdnews24.com)  The low over west central Bay and bordering northwest Bay weakened, a Bangladesh Meteorological Department bulletin Monday said. Another low that formed over the southeastern regions of Bangladesh and adjoining Bay area moved northwestward and laid over Barisal Monday morning, it said. The low is likely to intensify further into a land depression and move in a north-northwesterly direction. Monsoon is active over Bangladesh and strong over the north Bay. Squally weather may continue over the maritime ports. Sea will remain rough. Maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been advised to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number three. Under its influence, the low lying areas of the coastal districts of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar, Noakhali, Laxmipur, Bhola, Patuakhali, Barisal, Chandpur, Barguna, Pirozpur, Jhalokathi, Bagerhat, Khulna, Satkhira and the offshore inlands and shoals are likely to be inundated by wind-driven surge of 2-4 feet height above the normal astronomical tide. All fishing boats and trawlers cruising in the north Bay have been advised to take shelter immediately and remain in shelter until further notice. b
